      "description": "Planar double-box with five massive and one massless internal propagator, four external legs (three massless, one massive with $p_4^2=m_h^2$). Four master integrals; in $d=4$ one decouples and the remaining three reduce to a $2\\times 2$ coupled system (since $\\mathrm{Cut}(I_3)=0$). The second-order DE is solved by the maximal cut in terms of complete elliptic integrals $K(\\omega)$ where $\\omega = 16 m^2 \\sqrt{-s t u m_h^2} / [s(m_h^2-t)^2 - 4m^2(m_h^2(s-t)+t(s+t)-2 \\sqrt{-s t u m_h^2})]$.",
